Text: They brought the big guns too!? Gimme a break...
Hmmm, no clues here... Guess I'll keep looking.

Gobbie knows when
gobbie is outwhacked...
All gob, backfall!

Time of wordbond is over.
All gob, backfall!
By the will of the elementals!

And so it begins.
Are you ready?
They've grown bold to push this far.
Spread out, and be wary of artillery fire.
Keep to the north. We will head off their troops to the south.
Brace yourself. They've called for reinforcements!
Thanks, but we're not done yet.
Keep moving. We will hold them here!

Pshhh... Gobbies whack
for Falcons muchly!

Pshhh... Gobbies whack
for Ravens muchly!
To boom or not to boom?
You seem troubled, friends. Not getting tired, are you?
By the Fury! What is that?
Fear not! Help is on the way!
This is for you, old friend.
Behold the art of the shinobi!
Go on,  . Leave these soldiers to us.
Sellgob whack-ready! Whack and thwack for uplander!
For jinglyshine, gobbies frontcharge! Gobbies smashstrike!
It looks ready to explode. Stand back!
An explosive!? It must be stopped.
Such sweet blood, so very fresh. But...oh! Yours is fresher still...
I shall sup gently on your veins. So very gently...
Now see what you've done! Mine own blood is spilled! Mine...mine...MINE...
Friends! Partners! Come closer... See my wares! I bring only the finest.
Friends! Partners! A humble invitation─learn how this blade cuts!
Now, my partners! What do you offer in trade? One life, or more?
Miserly mortals! I ask for so little─only your lifeblood!
We probably shouldn't go barging in there alone, kupo!
This all feels familiar...like back in Ridorana...
I imagine this is what it is like to be swallowed by a morbol, kupo!
There are traces of aetherial residue here. Most likely from auracite, kupo.
The aether here is different. Is this...joy I feel, kupo?
This wine looks good enough to drink! Do you think we should─? No? Alright, kupo...
There is much pain in the aether here. A great loss, kupo...
Let me guess, someone from the Durai Papers, kupo?
I'm going to go out on a limb and guess this place is fairly old, kupo.
Might you recall earlier when I said the aether felt corrupted? Well, it's really corrupted now, kupo!
Mullonde? Now where have I heard that name before, kupo?
Wait... What is Cid doing down here, kupo?
Something is wrong... I sense both anguish and rapture, kupo!
You mustn't fear her! Leave that to me, kupo!
The time for games has passed.
Take it! This power of mine...
Now turn your gaze upon them! See the fools become as stone!
I know what you're thinking... “Man, that was cheap!” Sorry, so sorry!
The sands are thirsty for your blood!
Your corpse will feed my flames!
You fight bravely, but your time has come!
This is as far as you go!
The sky weeps burning tears to lament your passing!
That arcane circle is somehow connected to the auracite! I can feel it, kupo!

Fly my dearest daughter,
Flow my precious stream.♪

Rest but never wallow,
Lose not your purity.♪

Change always and forever,
And let your joy run deep.♪

Neneroon's claws made
for eating, not clawing...

Curses, it's still moving!
Keep cutting!
Time to demonstrate the fruits of my training!
Hm hm hm... I've had quite enough of you!
More! We want to see more!
What's that smell? Is something burning?

Seems we've driven
them off, though.
Keep them away from the carriage!
Shards of ice, pierce and slice!
Brilliant bolts, give them a jolt!
Again! Again and again and again!
That this should all be an illusion...
Watering the plants? Nay, strengthening them.
What magick is this that could create such a convincing illusion?
Another landscape... How much further to the crown, I wonder.
Never have I seen such mastery over glamours.
A Fuath! And it's...watering the plants?
More illusions? You have to hand it to them...
Real or no, it's beautiful beyond words...
The crown already? Forgive me if I'm suspicious.
So this is the realm of the water spirits...
Seems they don't mean to make this easy for us.
Ah, yes, the good old stop-them-with-wasps trick.
Naught here is what it seemeth. Tread warily.
The crown... With its protectors conspicuous in their absence...
Oh, my! Did you see the flowers?
A palace of water... It's like something out of a faerie tale...
It's like being in a dream...
Yet the dangers of this dream are very real. Be not distracted by its beauty.
Is that a Fuath? What is it doing?
Making their minions stronger, by the looks of it.
It seems they haven't quite had enough games.
They certainly have no shortage of ideas.
Except we're the ones in the tale. Stay on your guard.
No, stop! I smell a trap!
If it stands in our way, it falls like the rest.
No. It was just toying with us.
They recreated a legend, is that it?
Imitation will only take you so far.
This time we'll really have the crown!
Focus on the fight, Minfilia─not the prize.
It seems the statues aren't only for show.
Have care. I sense aether emanating from the statues...
Surely they wouldn't try the same trick twice?
Another array of statues. No doubt these too serve to guard our path.
More statues. Another trap, I should think.
Their leader, if I'm not mistaken. Ware its glamours.
Aye, but I doubt they would lay the same trap twice.
No beating about the bush with this one.
There's no getting around this one...
Its design calls to mind the Ronkan legends of giants. Fascinating...
The Ronkans guard their secrets well.
Finally. The way forward is open.
Though thankfully nowhere near the fabled might of Lozatl.
Truly a fascinating specimen of Ronkan ingenuity.
An earthquake? Nay. Something stirreth deep within...
I care not to see the source of these tremors.
On thy guard. Carelessness shall find no clemency here.
Stay on your guard. We near the tremors' source.
If you desire sport, we're happy to oblige!
That's a nice illusion, but you can't fool us!
So you're the one making all that racket?
The source of the ghastly wails and tremors both, 'twould seem.
That such a beast could survive down here all this time...
Any longer and I thought this cave might've collapsed.
Whence did the bat enter here, I wonder.
I fear my ears will be ringing for quite some time.
Would that we could stop and rest, but we must press on.
Sin eaters... Then our suspicions were correct.
Let's cut this overgrown scrub down to size.
Ah, the final form. Or should I say false form?
The sooner we get this over with, the better.
A rather nasty-looking thing, isn't it?
'Tis more terrible than the Viis described.
I can sense the Warden somewhere below us.
The ancients were well beyond their time.
Can you sense the Warden, Ryne?
Yes, but I think it's further underground.
This tunnel seems to stretch on forever...
It looks like we can descend from here.
What do you suppose we'll find down here?
Isn't that a little big for an armadillo?
That their chieftain should personally stand in our way...
Curious... Yonder creature doth resemble Griaule, a beast of Voeburtite legend.
'Twould seem we are come to the grand finale.
Shall we get this over and done with?
I would rather not slay the beast, but if it means to bar our way...
It's in the way is what it is.
If I never see an armadillo again...
Let us press onward. The Warden awaits.
A shame the miners haven't the means to keep building.
We need to climb down somehow.
Well there has to be a path somewhere...
With any luck this tunnel will lead down.
And into the heart of the Warden's lair.
Is this some sort of joke?
This certainly isn't what I was expecting.
Why, yes... Yes I believe they are...
I think I now understand Alphinaud's aversion to water.
I never knew buckets could be so dangerous.
Gods, I'm soaked to the bone.
These crystals are devoid of aether...
Terrible is the beast that doth wreak such corruption.
We're nearly there. I can feel it!
I have a bad feeling about these boulders...
Oh gods, the boulders. They're filling with light!
Careful. I sense something queer within these rocks.
Gods, is nothing safe from the sin eaters' corruption?
Let us be brief. The others are waiting.
Well done, Ryne. Now to end this.
You call this a paradise? Don't make me laugh!
Vauthry! I won't let you hurt anyone anymore!
This time he will not escape.
Oh dear, you made her mad. You're in for it now.
Well, that made short work of them!
Now that's what I call a helping hand!
Let us take care of the rest!
That affords us some room to breathe.
Hah, as if they were flies!
A blow struck for all who suffered under you!
Aye, let's make the most of it!
Like one of the guardians of Amdapor...
Ah, this fellow again. Just like old times.
I'm not afraid... I'm not afraid...
Oh, come now. We know this is an illusion.
Good thing I'm light on my feet.
Makes me feel dirty just to look at it...
A voidsent? Or yet another illusion?
I grow weary of these tricks!
This isn't like before. This time I'll fight too.
But this time I'll fight too!
I should like to study their link to the statues on the Source.
Nice to finally settle that old score.
Vauthry will need more than that to stop us.
Aye, nice to finally settle that old score.
A palace? Did Vauthry build this?
A gaudy palace... How like Vauthry.
All this via aetherial manipulation? Impressive...
Hmph, the man's vanity knows no bounds.
A cube-shaped eater. Perfect for blocking the way.
I'm just going to assume that cube is an eater.
Its form notwithstanding, I believe that is a sin eater.
Have care. It harbors a prodigious amount of aether.
There is much we do not know about sin eaters.
Phew, that was tougher than it looked...
I leave the cartridges to you!
And there I thought I'd seen them all.
By my reckoning, it was an elemental made eater.
No amount of splendor will make you king!
Oh, I look forward to shutting him up!
This place really isn't to my taste.
If you're righteous, why did you run?
A good thing we are here to tear it down.
This Light... Vauthry channels it into his minions!
He made them stronger, the bastard!
The sin eaters partake of their master's power...
This surging aether... Vauthry empowers his minions!
So much Light! Be careful, everyone!
Vauthry deigns to send us his favorite.
I'll take that to mean that we're close!
Such aether... It could be a Warden in its own right!
So it's a bigger candle than most. We'll snuff it out.
Off it goes... It seems we must do more to earn the crown.

I see storms of emotion...
The aether here is seething with it.

Steady, Ryne!
Remember: this is only a recreation!

Watch where you step!
Ware the falling flames!
I know the beasts are eye-catching, but keep watch for those meteors!
A city burneth 'neath fiery skies, and calamitous beasts hold sway...
It's like seeing the stars fall from the sky...
...Like the pages of a myth come to life.
This first doom seemed deadly enough not to warrant a second...
Even knowing it's all illusion makes it no less terrifying...
Time for another type of ammunition.
...And that was but the first doom they faced?
A horror to beget an even greater abomination...
There goes a tower! We'll run out of walkway at this rate...

Creation magicks run rampant...
'Tis the stuff of nightmares.

Watch out!
We'll be lucky not to get crushed...
Nay, he will make certain we see it all. He wants us to see...
This is almost too much to witness...but witness it we must.
Seven hells! These beasts lurk behind every stone!
To die by fire, or by fang...
This beast falleth short of the legend.
Aye, and we'd best keep moving if we're to avoid a similar fate.
A terror of a different hue...
Is this another of these dooms, then?

A man's face on a bird's body...
How unsettling.
The form fear taketh is unlike to be pleasing.
The beasts are links in a chain of fear...yet we seem to have broken it.
These battles test the boundaries of our stamina...
This time, mayhap. I worry we might not outlast the next.
Have we ascended into the heavens themselves!?

I-Is that the star!?
The whole world is ablaze...

Ah, Master Matoya...
If only you could see this...
We perceive the scene from the heavens, as the Ascians did.

The final doom...
The largest was saved for last, it seems.
I don't care how monstrous it is! We end this now!

Ignore my trembling!
I can fight! I've made my choice...
This is the final doom, yes? Then let us be about defeating it!
Ryne! How are you holding up?
I can do this! We can do this! Together!

Oh gods, that sin eater...
It can't be...

Look! Over there...
Does it yet hunt for prey?
They swell their ranks with wild beasts...
I fear for the village. Let us make short work of these!

I knew it!
That's the eater from Amh Araeng!

Ready yourselves!
This is no lesser spawn!
We'll not slip past this one. To arms!
This is the monster we saw in Amh Araeng!

Easy now, Alisaie.
We face it together!
No match for us, it seems...

The fiend is slain.
Let us press on, shall we?

Survivors!
We must buy them time to flee!
Go! Take refuge in the Crystarium!

Steel your hearts.
There may be others we can save.
Aye, we draw the eaters to us!

It seems confused.
It must be newly turned...
We leave none behind us. Put it down.
Is there no end to this place?
I pray that trap was the last...
We must find a place to hide.
Damn it! We need to hurry!
Is this the end for us...?
What does it mean to do?
Behind Cylva! We must brace for the attack!

Heh heh heh...
No one will save you!

Futile!
All you do is in vain!
Heh... That was a close one.
Zzzkrrrt... That power belongs to me!
Get to the carriage in front!
We'll be fine! Do as you must!
Leave this to us! Go on, crack a few skulls for me!
No, really─we're quite all right, I assure you!
Head north─that's where you're needed most!
Fear not, we have the situation well in hand.
Go on! There's no time to waste!
Here─this should keep you in the fight!
Become blazing stars and smite my foes!
I-I have the two of you. I'll be fine...I think.
Don't die! If you do, I'll be next!
My hunger is far from slaked!
What have you done to me...

No more pain where
you are now, I pray...
I had hoped to refrain from drastic measures...
What is the meaning of this!?
I shall tend to your wounds!
Who dares disturb the peace of Gridania!?
Keep yer mitts off me mackerel!
I do not like the look of thisss!
Those benthos got me... Losing too much blood...
I am afraid I will only get in your way...
May the breath of the earth relieve us of our burdens!
There'll be nothing left of you but a smoking crater!
The best defense is a good defense!
Our fates are not yet sealed.
O radiant starlight, become my blade!
All that I have and more, I bring to bear!
The stars shall grant thee succor.
Thy time hath not yet come.
Oh Mother Hydaelyn, grant us succor that we may rise anew!
This is going to leave a mark!
You will rue the day you crossed my path!
You may be surprised by what I can do...
This villain is not without his tricks!
Focus on the task at hand!
May the power of the Crystal keep us from harm!
May the Crystal's fire rain down upon our foe!
May the Crystal's mercy mend our hurts!
Don't say I didn't warn you!
Why do you persist in this folly?
Beast of my blood, answer my call!
Rend my foes and ward their blows.
You would be wise to fear me!
And you presume to be her protector. Pathetic!
Take this! And that! And this!
I have something special in store for you!
Let us see how you handle this!
Right, no more Missus Nice Jester!

Hobgoblins!
They've come for the catch!

There are too many of them!
Hide the children!
We are saved! A thousand thousand blessings upon you!
You shall live on in Ondo legend for eternity!
This will work, I know it!
Do you really think this will hold me?
Now that's taken care of, it's back to the fray!
I thought we had already burned this thing once!
Yes, we set it ablaze, I am sure of it!
If fire has no effect, we will have to try something else!
I hope we never have to face a foe like that again.
Hmm... Nothing out of the ordinary.
Gods be good... There are too many of them!
There is nothing we can do. Retreat!
To think the Children could raise such beasts...
The Children and their vile pets deserve each other!
Poison spreads just like a disease, doesn't it?
Why do the birds keep eating them!?
Perhaps I need a better plan of action...
The place looks much tidier now, if nothing else.
A few more of these, and I think we consider the job done.
Have you found any? If so, give them to me!
There are things I'd rather be doing, I assure you!
If the flamingos have swallowed any fragments, we'll need to retrieve those, too!
Ungh! A whole pack of them!
We cannot let them near Slitherbough!
Fall back! We must call for reinforcements!
